Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of a framework for social semantic portals that support users in interacting with STEM documents. This involves the use of MKM technologies and eMath3.0 portals, which are related to digital libraries (cs.DL), computational complexity (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
